snippet: The peak of the sunspot cycle has produced few spectacular bursts, and much speculation about how much more can be expected.
abstract: Peak of 11-year sunspot cycle, when the sun erupts with solar flares and energetic burst of electrons and protons, has been quieter than initially predicted by scientists; experts note, however, that quiet cycles are not unusual, and that some of the biggest solar storms sometimes occur on the way down; cycle has taught researchers that they still have much to learn about the sun.
lead_paragraph: The peak of the sunspot cycle has produced few spectacular bursts, and much speculation about how much more can be expected.

headline.main: A Solar Show With Mixed Reviews
